    {
      "name": "Soren",
      "race": "Custom Lineage",
      "classes": [
        {
          "name": "Barbarian",
          "level": 6,
          "subclassName": "Path of the Totem Warrior",
          "subclassDescription": "<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The Path of the Totem Warrior is a spiritual journey, as the barbarian accepts a spirit animal as guide, protector, and inspiration. In battle, your totem spirit fills you with supernatural might, adding magical fuel to your ba<span class=\"No-Break\">rbarian rage.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">In some barbarians’ tribes, a totem animal is considered to be kin to a particular clan. In such cases, it is unusual for an individual to have more than one totem animal spirit, though exce<span class=\"No-Break\">ptions exist.</span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "alignmentId": 4,
      "background": null,
      "personalityTraits": "Initially distant and cold, but when once she considers someone her family, she's loyal and fiercely protective. Due to the harsh conditions of her homeland, she's inflexible and stuck in her ways since they were essential to survival.",
      "ideals": "Family and loyalty. Her sense of duty to her tribe and peoples.\nGreater Good. It is each person’s responsibility to make the most happiness for the whole tribe. (Good)\nMight. The strongest are meant to rule. (Evil)",
      "bonds": "My family, clan, or tribe is the most important thing in my life, even when they are far from me.",
      "flaws": "Stubborn and inflexible. Prejudiced from life on the tundra.\nI am slow to trust members of other races, tribes, and societies.",
      "backstory": null,
      "otherNotes": "Cleave\nThe Cleave property allows you to use heavy weapons to hit multiple opponents with one massive swing. Whenever you hit a creature with a Melee Weapon Attack, you can make another Melee Attack Roll to hit a second creature you can see within 5ft of the first. On a hit, your second target takes damage equal to the weapon without any additional Ability Modifier damage (unless your modifier is negative). Ideal for crowd control situations, the cleave property is a go-to for those looking to carve through large swaths of enemies. ",
